            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9 billion provides the resources necessary to meet the scientific community's peer-reviewed priorities established in the National Academies Decadal Surveys.\n* Restoring funding levels prevents the loss of hard-won technical expertise and infrastructure following the pressure of previous budget cuts.\n* NASA Science is the agency's most popular activity in public polling, reflecting broad non-partisan support for exploration and discovery.",
